{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1956","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1956/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1956/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1956/events","html_url":"https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/issues/1956","id":1744963120,"node_id":"I_kwDOBEVPe85oAgYw","number":1956,"title":"Out of place exponential Krylov regression","user":{"login":"ChrisRackauckas","id":1814174,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4MTQxNzQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1814174?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas","html_url":"https://github.com/ChrisRackauckas","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ChrisRackauckas/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2023-06-07T03:28:06Z","updated_at":"2023-06-07T20:19:29Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"In https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/pull/1951 it was found that the linear Krylov tests were failing. https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/pull/1954 showed that those tests were failing on master. The last major change to this part of the code was https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/pull/1917, which makes sense because the Krylov methods use the SciMLOperators directly, so something must have happened with the OOP definition of `*` and its usage from SplitODEFunction.

In the code, there was an issue that was found that it didn't have an OOP update_func, https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/master/test/algconvergence/linear_nonlinear_krylov_tests.jl#L19 which meant it wasn't testing much. This needed a fix in https://github.com/SciML/SciMLBase.jl/commit/e4f2a5a3f4414941b2c365b3c5733eb9940c9f3f so the jac was correct, and then it was noticed that the values were off. Now 
 https://github.com/SciML/OrdinaryDiffEq.jl/blob/master/test/algconvergence/linear_nonlinear_krylov_tests.jl has the OOP tests in skip mode, but this is a pretty bad regression so we should make sure this gets a good look ASAP. I think it would be hard to revert the SciMLOperators + SparseDiffTools + LinearSolve updates, so I think we just need to figure out what regressed and handle it.

